  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (expanded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Following regulatory clearance, the indicated patient population was extended to include pediatric patients (body surface area 0.5–1.0 m²) operating at reduced flow rates (1.0–2.2 L/min), a regime not represented in the original validation campaign. The assessment team concluded that the existing validation evidence, obtained at adult flow rates (3.5–6.0 L/min) on the same pump geometry, is sufficiently conservative to bound pediatric hemolysis predictions without additional experimental test points.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-claim-001",
