      "rationale": "All five adult validation test points were conducted with calibrated Coriolis flow meters (±1.2% accuracy) and controlled hematocrit (35 ± 2%). Simulation boundary conditions set to measured values. Pediatric flow regime (1.0–2.2 L/min) was not included in the experimental campaign; the team asserts that the fluid properties and geometric boundary conditions remain identical and that extrapolation is reasonable."
