      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on the same pump geometry, same fluid analog, and operating conditions spanning the COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the physical FDA GCBP test article with porcine blood analog at adult CPB flow rates. Pump geometry and fluid analog are identical to the deployment configuration. The pediatric sub-population operates the same physical device; the assessment team contends that the adult validation activities are directly relevant and that no additional validation activities are required, citing geometric and fluid similarity. The expanded pediatric flow range (1.0–2.2 L/min) falls outside the validated operating points but is treated as covered by the existing evidence without supplementary test data."
